I have recently started a monk, and nerf or no nerf, I will most likely spend most of my time soloing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  My main is a 56 Necro, so my monk, now 27, is pretty ok equipped for his level. <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=424646">Magelo Here</a><br>
<br>
 I do have a few questions with regard to monks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
At what point does more AGI become negligable? I read here that there is little benefit in having over 130, but was told by someone that it does make a difference.<br>
<br>
2-Hb - How do you get over the fact that some of the 2hb weapons in the list under the equipment forum weigh rather a lot?  A 2hb that weighs 10.0 does not to me seem like something a monk would consider.  Also, I haven't so far really used 2hb ( it's at 2 currently ), my intention being to dump a load of training points into it when i can afford an okay 2hb - is there a point (level) when it becomes a far better option that duel wielding?.<br>
<br>
Primary duel wield weapon - what is *more* important for the soloist - speed or ratio?<br>
<br>
On a plus note, I was soloing in Marus Seru last night and went to pull a rockhopper.  Closest to me were two.  So I thought that I would practice Intimidation (at 19) on one of them while I waited for one to wander off.  To my utter astonishment, not only did it work, I got a skill increase <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
thanks in advance for any answers <p><select>
