<br>
as for agi, i wouldn't worry about getting it up but rather get ac/hp/sta items instead and let agi be a byproduct (unless someone can post some info post-nerf that agi is now something to be wanting to get up)<br>
<br>
as for soloing any more,   heh  good luck there<br>
<br>
<br>
for 1h weapons you want your Fastest weapon in your main hand while having one with a good ratio in the offhand <p><b><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=197082">Brother Fryarr</a></b> <BR>
60 Monk<BR>
   <img src=http://www.sgtfuzzbubble99.homestead.com/files/Smilies/Sarge/MrT_anim.gif gif></img></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaleb123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daleb123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 349<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/18/02 2:49:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1969.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 2H Blunt</span><hr size=1> &quot;How do you get over the fact that some of the 2hb weapons in the list under the equipment forum weigh rather a lot?&quot;<br>
<br>
I don't use the ones that weight a lot. In a group, if I use a slow 2-hander while the primary tank dual wields a pair of nice, fast 1-handers, it won't matter so much - but soloing, you do not want to use a heavy weapon. Choose a lightweight 2HB weapon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucromulent357.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cromulent357</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/18/02 8:43:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1969.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2H Blunt</span><hr size=1> tstaff = 10lbs, but most high end monks have their weight pretty low due to high end items that are 0.1 or 0.0 lbs, and increases in their weight allowance (ie lvl 60 = 24lbs).<br>
<br>
Anyways, at your lvl, being a couple lbs overweight won't make much of a difference, so I wouldn't worry too much about buying a 2hb that seems heavy. I would start worrying a lot about weight when yer 40+, either pulling harder hitting mobs, or soloing them as well. <p><p align=center><b>Cromulent Mcgarnacle</b><Br><b>60 Grandmaster Monk</b><Br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=144144>Inspect My Dingleberries!!</a><Br><a href=http://www.dbguild.net>Enchanted Dragons</a><Br><a href=http://www.abbasite.com><b>ABBA LIVES!!</b></a><Br><a href=http://www.davidhasselhoff.com><b>Click here for David Hasselhoff!</b></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubamfort.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bamfort</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.phantommessenger.com/bamfort/smyin.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 773<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/18/02 11:31:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1969.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.phantommessenger.com/bamfort/pooh-zen.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2H Blunt</span><hr size=1> To skill up your 2hb, get a Bamboo Bo Stick.  It's light, cheap and fast. <p><center><table border=0><tr><td valign=bottom align=right width=200 bgcolor="#778899"><b><a href="http://www.phantommessenger.com/bamfort/"><font size="-1" color="#8b1a1a" face="comic sans ms">Bamfort Maldwitt</font></a></b><br><b><font color="#003366">Monk of the Ashen Order</font></b></td><td rowspan=2 align=middle valign=middle bgcolor="#000000"><img src="http://www.phantommessenger.com/bamfort/kungfu8.jpg"></td><td bgcolor="#778899" valign=bottom align=left width=200><b><font color="#003366">51st Koan of Meditation</font></b><br><font size="-1" color="#8b1a1a" face="comic sans ms"><b>Bristlebane</b></font></td></tr><tr><td align=right bgcolor="#778899"><a href="http://www.chaosmystic.com/crimsonblade/"><font face="comic sans ms" color="crimson" size="1"><b>Crimson</b></font></a></td><td align=left bgcolor="#778899"><a href="http://www.chaosmystic.com/crimsonblade/"><font face="comic sans ms" color="crimson" size="1"><b> Blade </b></font></a></td></tr><tr><td align=middle colspan=3 bgcolor="#778899"><font face="comic sans ms" color="#003366" size="-1">Bursting forth with the power of ten <b>billion</b> <font color="#ff7777">b</font><font color="#ffff80">u</font><font color="#3ec0ff">t</font><font color="#ff75ff">t</font><font color="gold">e</font><font color="#ff75ff">r</font><font color="#3ec0ff">f</font><font color="#ffff80">l</font><font color="#ff7777">y</font> sneezes<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=558" target="_blank">My Magelo Profile</a> || <a href="http://www.phantommessenger.com/bamfort" target="_blank">My Homemade Profile</a></font></td></tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukurrlee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kurrlee</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1082<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/18/02 12:12:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1969.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A few questions from a new monk</span><hr size=1> Bambo Bo is great for skilling up in 2HB. It also has the benefit (IIRC) of having a relativly small delay for a 2HB.<br>
<br>
Another overlooked 2HB is the Adamantite Bo. Not sure what the weight is but it is what I used from about 25-45.<br>
<br>
AGI will always give you benefit. I think the calculation is 3AGI for 1 AC. Maybe at higher numbers the calc changes to 4 or 5 AGI for 1 AC.<br>
<br>
The important numbers for all stats are 75 100 and 120. You will get more benefit from going from 74 to 75 than you will from going from 75 to 76. At 27 just try to keep all of your numbers above 100.<br>
<br>
In your primary hand you want your fastest weapon. In your off-hand you want the most highest damage weapon. <p>Kurrlee<br>
Shackle Of Tynnonium</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umouse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mouse</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://people.netscape.com/rowley/pete.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/18/02 3:14:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1969.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> For soloing I prefer 1 hnd</span><hr size=1> Purely due to the lower delays giving more predictable damage with less spikes (runs of misses).  3 or 4 misses on a slow high damage weapon can mean the difference between winning and feigning, this is rarely the case with low delay weapons.<br>
<br>
In assition I didn't nother with 2hb at all until the mid 50's when I scored a bamboo bo stick for 10pp, and raised the skill from 0 to around 150 in about a couple of hours in an exp group (which I was pulling for so my damage was in spurts anyway).  Then a bit later I got an IFS which I use for exp groups, I use epic + SoS for duoing (I never really solo unless caught unawares) and when I need more taunt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=1969.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showNextMessage?topicID=1969.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1969.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.emailToFriend?topicID=1969.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.threadControl?topicID=1969.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1969.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1969.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSF